Oshiomhole, a former governor of Edo State, polled 107,110 votes to defeat the incumbent, Francis Alimikhena of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). Adams Oshiomhole, former national chairman of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC), wins election to represent Edo north senatorial district at the National Assembly. Oshiomhole, a former governor of Edo State, polled 107,110 votes to defeat the incumbent, Francis Alimikhena of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). Alimikhena polled 55,344 votes in the election.